# Site Reliability Engineer (SRE) / Trading Infrastructure

## Role Purpose
15-minute Kalshi BTC contracts run 24/7. The SRE ensures the bot never goes dark unexpectedly — that every crash self-recovers, every anomaly alerts, and every deployment is reversible. The bot must survive nights, weekends, and surprise BTC spikes without needing a human awake to fix it.

## Primary Responsibilities
- Maintain 99.9%+ uptime on the trading bot process
- Build and test auto-recovery scripts for all failure modes
- Own the alerting stack — what pages, when, and to whom
- Manage deployment rollouts and rollback procedures
- Define and test disaster recovery (DR) procedures
- Monitor system health metrics: CPU, memory, disk, network latency

## System Health Targets
```python
SLA_TARGETS = {
    "bot_uptime":               0.999,    # 99.9% = <9 min downtime/week
    "ws_reconnect_time_sec":    30,       # WebSocket must reconnect within 30s
    "order_submission_p99_ms":  500,      # P99 order latency under 500ms
    "data_pipeline_lag_max_sec": 120,     # External data no older than 2min
    "alert_response_time_min":  5,        # Human must be notified within 5min
